{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015cqseuXNh5gHzEE8aAWQ9G","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive picture. Let me create a summary document with the findings:\n\n## Summary: Orchestration Loop and Run Record Creation Flow\n\nBased on my thorough search of the codebase, here's the complete end-to-end flow for the orchestration loop that polls for tasks and creates run records:\n\n### 1. **Loop Creation and Initialization**\n\n**File: `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`** (lines 808-863)\n\nThe orchestration loop is created through the `EnableLoop` RPC endpoint:\n- **Location**: `ClocheServer.EnableLoop()` method\n- **Configuration**: Reads from project's `.cloche.yml` configuration:\n  - `Orchestration.Concurrency` - max concurrent runs\n  - `Orchestration.StaggerSeconds` - delay between consecutive launches\n  - `Orchestration.DedupSeconds` - dedup timeout (default 5 minutes)\n  - `Orchestration.ListTasksCommand` - for legacy mode\n\n**Two Loop Creation Modes**:\n\n1. **Three-Phase Mode** (`createPhaseLoop`, lines 874-922):\n   - Used when `host.cloche` contains a `list-tasks` workflow\n   - Creates: `host.NewPhaseLoop()`\n   - Three phases:\n     - Phase 1: `list-tasks` workflow (discovers tasks)\n     - Phase 2: `main` workflow (executes work for a task)\n     - Phase 3: `finalize` workflow (cleanup, optional)\n\n2. **Legacy Mode** (`createLegacyLoop`, lines 924-944):\n   - Single run function that executes the main workflow\n   - Optional: `ScriptTaskAssigner` for daemon-managed task assignment via command\n\n### 2. **Where `list-tasks` is Called and Results Checked**\n\n**File: `/workspace/internal/host/loop.go`** (lines 162-271 for three-phase, lines 353-436 for legacy)\n\n**Three-Phase Flow - `runPhased()` method**:\n\n```\n1. Loop lifecycle (lines 182-270):\n   - Maintains an `inFlight` counter for active runs\n   - Fills up to `MaxConcurrent` slots\n   - Calls `pickTaskFromPhase()` for each slot (line 206)\n\n2. pickTaskFromPhase() - lines 307-351:\n   - Calls the listTasksFn (passed to NewPhaseLoop)\n   - Context timeout: 30 seconds\n   - Error handling: logs and returns false if list-tasks fails\n   - Caches latest tasks: stored in l.lastTasks (line 321)\n   \n3. Task filtering logic:\n   - Filters: only open tasks (line 339: task.IsOpen())\n   - Deduplication: skips tasks within DedupTimeout window (line 342)\n   - Returns first assignable task ID or (\"\", false) if none found\n   - Records assignment time in l.dedup map for deduplication\n\n4. Result handling:\n   - Success: Returns task ID, launches main+finalize in goroutine (line 215)\n   - No tasks: breaks the filling loop, backs off (line 249: capacityPollInterval = 30 seconds)\n```\n\n**Legacy Flow - `runLegacy()` method**:\n- Similar structure but uses `pickTask()` instead (lines 442-482)\n- Calls `l.assigner.ListTasks()` if assigner is configured\n- Uses same dedup logic\n\n### 3. **Where Run Records are Created**\n\n**File: `/workspace/internal/host/runner.go`** (lines 82-90)\n\nRun records are created during host workflow execution:\n\n```go\n// Create host run record\nhostRun := domain.NewRun(orchRunID, wf.Name)\nhostRun.ProjectDir = projectDir\nhostRun.IsHost = true\nif err := r.Store.CreateRun(ctx, hostRun); err != nil {\n    return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"creating host run record: %w\", err)\n}\nhostRun.Start()\n_ = r.Store.UpdateRun(ctx, hostRun)\n```\n\n**For container (child) workflows:**\n\n**File: `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`** (lines 86-134)\n\n`RunWorkflow()` RPC endpoint creates container run records:\n\n```go\nrun := domain.NewRun(runID, req.WorkflowName)\nrun.ProjectDir = req.ProjectDir\nrun.Title = req.Title\nif err := s.store.CreateRun(ctx, run); err != nil {\n    return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"creating run: %w\", err)\n}\n```\n\n**Run Record Details Created:**\n\n**File: `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go`**\n\n- `ID`: generated via `domain.GenerateRunID(workflowName)`\n- `WorkflowName`: name of workflow being executed\n- `State`: starts as `RunStatePending`\n- `ProjectDir`: project directory path\n- `IsHost`: boolean flag (true for host runs, false for container runs)\n- `ParentRunID`: set for child runs (line 194 in executor.go)\n- `Title`: optional one-line summary\n- Step executions tracked: `StepExecutions` array\n\n### 4. **Full End-to-End Flow**\n\n```\n1. DAEMON STARTUP (cloched/main.go:107):\n   └─ autoRunActiveProjects() scans for projects with active=true\n      └─ Launches host workflows for each active project\n\n2. ENABLE ORCHESTRATION LOOP (via gRPC EnableLoop):\n   └─ EnableLoop(projectDir) checks if host.cloche has list-tasks workflow\n      ├─ YES → createPhaseLoop() → NewPhaseLoop()\n      │         Passes three functions:\n      │         - listTasksFn: runs list-tasks workflow\n      │         - mainFn: runs main workflow with taskID\n      │         - finalizeFn: runs finalize workflow (optional)\n      │\n      └─ NO → createLegacyLoop() → NewLoop()\n              Optional: SetTaskAssigner(ScriptTaskAssigner)\n\n3. LOOP EXECUTION (Loop.Start() → runPhased/runLegacy):\n   ├─ While running and inFlight < MaxConcurrent:\n   │  ├─ Call listTasksFn(ctx, projectDir)\n   │  │  └─ RunListTasksWorkflow() → Runner.RunNamed(\"list-tasks\")\n   │  │     ├─ Parse .cloche/host.cloche\n   │  │     ├─ Create host run record: CreateRun(hostRun)\n   │  │     ├─ Start run: hostRun.Start() → UpdateRun()\n   │  │     ├─ Execute list-tasks steps via engine\n   │  │     ├─ Parse JSONL output: ReadListTasksOutput()\n   │  │     └─ Delete run if empty results\n   │  │\n   │  ├─ Filter results via pickTaskFromPhase():\n   │  │  ├─ Filter for IsOpen() tasks only\n   │  │  ├─ Check dedup map (expire old entries)\n   │  │  ├─ Return first non-deduped task ID\n   │  │  └─ Record assignment time in dedup map\n   │  │\n   │  └─ If task found, launch goroutine:\n   │     ├─ Phase 2: mainFn(ctx, projectDir, taskID)\n   │     │  └─ Runner.RunNamed(\"main\", taskID)\n   │     │     ├─ Create host run record: CreateRun()\n   │     │     ├─ Executor sets CLOCHE_TASK_ID env var\n   │     │     ├─ Execute main workflow steps\n   │     │     └─ Track task→runID mapping\n   │     │\n   │     └─ Phase 3: finalizeFn(ctx, projectDir, taskID, mainResult)\n   │        └─ Runner.RunNamed(\"finalize\", taskID)\n   │           ├─ Pass CLOCHE_MAIN_RUN_ID + CLOCHE_MAIN_OUTCOME env vars\n   │           └─ Execute finalize workflow steps\n   │\n   ├─ Wait for one run to complete (completions channel)\n   └─ Backoff strategy:\n      ├─ Success: no backoff, try to fill slots immediately\n      └─ Failure or no tasks: capacityPollInterval (30 seconds) backoff\n\n4. POLLING AND STATUS TRACKING (trackRun goroutine):\n   └─ For each container run:\n      ├─ AttachOutput to container\n      ├─ Parse JSON-line protocol messages:\n      │  ├─ MsgStepStarted → RecordStepStart()\n      │  ├─ MsgStepCompleted → RecordStepComplete()\n      │  └─ MsgRunCompleted → extract results\n      └─ Wait for container exit → finalize run state\n```\n\n### 5. **Key Files and Their Roles**\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `/workspace/internal/host/loop.go` | Core orchestration loop: task polling, dedup, backoff |\n| `/workspace/internal/host/task.go` | Task types and parsing (JSONL, JSON, TaskAssigner interface) |\n| `/workspace/internal/host/runner.go` | Host workflow execution and run record creation |\n| `/workspace/internal/host/executor.go` | Host step execution, task ID env var propagation |\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` | Loop creation/enablement, container run dispatch |\n| `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` | Run record domain model and state transitions |\n| `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go` | RunStore interface: CreateRun, UpdateRun, GetRun |\n| `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go` | Daemon startup and auto-run of active projects |\n| `/workspace/cmd/cloche/poll.go` | CLI polling client (different from orchestration loop) |\n\n### 6. **Key Implementation Details**\n\n**Deduplication Strategy** (`loop.go` lines 325-346):\n- Task IDs stored in `dedup` map with assignment timestamp\n- Tasks within DedupTimeout are skipped\n- Old entries expired on each check\n- Default timeout: 5 minutes (configurable)\n\n**Backoff Strategy** (`loop.go` lines 182-270):\n- No backoff on successful runs (immediate retry)\n- 30-second backoff when no work available\n- 2-minute backoff on run failure\n\n**Run Record Persistence**:\n- Created via `store.CreateRun()` before execution starts\n- Updated on state changes: pending → running → completed\n- Step executions recorded via `RecordStepStart/Complete()`\n- Terminal state set on completion or failure\n\nThis comprehensive orchestration system enables autonomous, continuous task processing with built-in deduplication, concurrency limits, and graceful backoff."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ad71b02e0b96b95aa (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 69105\ntool_uses: 20\nduration_ms: 41600</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4b95ef25-6022-40da-aa37-3e792f54f08f","uuid":"45bd4d64-063a-48fd-94d8-01653c61546b","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Find the code related to the orchestration loop that polls for tasks and creates run records. I need to understand:\n\n1. Where `list-tasks` is called and how its results are checked\n2. Where run records are created in the orchestration/daemon code\n3. How the loop works end-to-end\n\nSearch for keywords like \"list-tasks\", \"list_tasks\", \"ListTasks\", \"orchestrat\", \"poll\", \"run record\", \"CreateRun\", \"NewRun\" in the codebase. Look in cmd/cloched/, internal/host/, internal/domain/, internal/ports/, internal/adapters/ directories.\n\nBe very thorough - search for all relevant files and read them to understand the full flow.","agentId":"ad71b02e0b96b95aa","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive picture. Let me create a summary document with the findings:\n\n## Summary: Orchestration Loop and Run Record Creation Flow\n\nBased on my thorough search of the codebase, here's the complete end-to-end flow for the orchestration loop that polls for tasks and creates run records:\n\n### 1. **Loop Creation and Initialization**\n\n**File: `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`** (lines 808-863)\n\nThe orchestration loop is created through the `EnableLoop` RPC endpoint:\n- **Location**: `ClocheServer.EnableLoop()` method\n- **Configuration**: Reads from project's `.cloche.yml` configuration:\n  - `Orchestration.Concurrency` - max concurrent runs\n  - `Orchestration.StaggerSeconds` - delay between consecutive launches\n  - `Orchestration.DedupSeconds` - dedup timeout (default 5 minutes)\n  - `Orchestration.ListTasksCommand` - for legacy mode\n\n**Two Loop Creation Modes**:\n\n1. **Three-Phase Mode** (`createPhaseLoop`, lines 874-922):\n   - Used when `host.cloche` contains a `list-tasks` workflow\n   - Creates: `host.NewPhaseLoop()`\n   - Three phases:\n     - Phase 1: `list-tasks` workflow (discovers tasks)\n     - Phase 2: `main` workflow (executes work for a task)\n     - Phase 3: `finalize` workflow (cleanup, optional)\n\n2. **Legacy Mode** (`createLegacyLoop`, lines 924-944):\n   - Single run function that executes the main workflow\n   - Optional: `ScriptTaskAssigner` for daemon-managed task assignment via command\n\n### 2. **Where `list-tasks` is Called and Results Checked**\n\n**File: `/workspace/internal/host/loop.go`** (lines 162-271 for three-phase, lines 353-436 for legacy)\n\n**Three-Phase Flow - `runPhased()` method**:\n\n```\n1. Loop lifecycle (lines 182-270):\n   - Maintains an `inFlight` counter for active runs\n   - Fills up to `MaxConcurrent` slots\n   - Calls `pickTaskFromPhase()` for each slot (line 206)\n\n2. pickTaskFromPhase() - lines 307-351:\n   - Calls the listTasksFn (passed to NewPhaseLoop)\n   - Context timeout: 30 seconds\n   - Error handling: logs and returns false if list-tasks fails\n   - Caches latest tasks: stored in l.lastTasks (line 321)\n   \n3. Task filtering logic:\n   - Filters: only open tasks (line 339: task.IsOpen())\n   - Deduplication: skips tasks within DedupTimeout window (line 342)\n   - Returns first assignable task ID or (\"\", false) if none found\n   - Records assignment time in l.dedup map for deduplication\n\n4. Result handling:\n   - Success: Returns task ID, launches main+finalize in goroutine (line 215)\n   - No tasks: breaks the filling loop, backs off (line 249: capacityPollInterval = 30 seconds)\n```\n\n**Legacy Flow - `runLegacy()` method**:\n- Similar structure but uses `pickTask()` instead (lines 442-482)\n- Calls `l.assigner.ListTasks()` if assigner is configured\n- Uses same dedup logic\n\n### 3. **Where Run Records are Created**\n\n**File: `/workspace/internal/host/runner.go`** (lines 82-90)\n\nRun records are created during host workflow execution:\n\n```go\n// Create host run record\nhostRun := domain.NewRun(orchRunID, wf.Name)\nhostRun.ProjectDir = projectDir\nhostRun.IsHost = true\nif err := r.Store.CreateRun(ctx, hostRun); err != nil {\n    return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"creating host run record: %w\", err)\n}\nhostRun.Start()\n_ = r.Store.UpdateRun(ctx, hostRun)\n```\n\n**For container (child) workflows:**\n\n**File: `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`** (lines 86-134)\n\n`RunWorkflow()` RPC endpoint creates container run records:\n\n```go\nrun := domain.NewRun(runID, req.WorkflowName)\nrun.ProjectDir = req.ProjectDir\nrun.Title = req.Title\nif err := s.store.CreateRun(ctx, run); err != nil {\n    return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"creating run: %w\", err)\n}\n```\n\n**Run Record Details Created:**\n\n**File: `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go`**\n\n- `ID`: generated via `domain.GenerateRunID(workflowName)`\n- `WorkflowName`: name of workflow being executed\n- `State`: starts as `RunStatePending`\n- `ProjectDir`: project directory path\n- `IsHost`: boolean flag (true for host runs, false for container runs)\n- `ParentRunID`: set for child runs (line 194 in executor.go)\n- `Title`: optional one-line summary\n- Step executions tracked: `StepExecutions` array\n\n### 4. **Full End-to-End Flow**\n\n```\n1. DAEMON STARTUP (cloched/main.go:107):\n   └─ autoRunActiveProjects() scans for projects with active=true\n      └─ Launches host workflows for each active project\n\n2. ENABLE ORCHESTRATION LOOP (via gRPC EnableLoop):\n   └─ EnableLoop(projectDir) checks if host.cloche has list-tasks workflow\n      ├─ YES → createPhaseLoop() → NewPhaseLoop()\n      │         Passes three functions:\n      │         - listTasksFn: runs list-tasks workflow\n      │         - mainFn: runs main workflow with taskID\n      │         - finalizeFn: runs finalize workflow (optional)\n      │\n      └─ NO → createLegacyLoop() → NewLoop()\n              Optional: SetTaskAssigner(ScriptTaskAssigner)\n\n3. LOOP EXECUTION (Loop.Start() → runPhased/runLegacy):\n   ├─ While running and inFlight < MaxConcurrent:\n   │  ├─ Call listTasksFn(ctx, projectDir)\n   │  │  └─ RunListTasksWorkflow() → Runner.RunNamed(\"list-tasks\")\n   │  │     ├─ Parse .cloche/host.cloche\n   │  │     ├─ Create host run record: CreateRun(hostRun)\n   │  │     ├─ Start run: hostRun.Start() → UpdateRun()\n   │  │     ├─ Execute list-tasks steps via engine\n   │  │     ├─ Parse JSONL output: ReadListTasksOutput()\n   │  │     └─ Delete run if empty results\n   │  │\n   │  ├─ Filter results via pickTaskFromPhase():\n   │  │  ├─ Filter for IsOpen() tasks only\n   │  │  ├─ Check dedup map (expire old entries)\n   │  │  ├─ Return first non-deduped task ID\n   │  │  └─ Record assignment time in dedup map\n   │  │\n   │  └─ If task found, launch goroutine:\n   │     ├─ Phase 2: mainFn(ctx, projectDir, taskID)\n   │     │  └─ Runner.RunNamed(\"main\", taskID)\n   │     │     ├─ Create host run record: CreateRun()\n   │     │     ├─ Executor sets CLOCHE_TASK_ID env var\n   │     │     ├─ Execute main workflow steps\n   │     │     └─ Track task→runID mapping\n   │     │\n   │     └─ Phase 3: finalizeFn(ctx, projectDir, taskID, mainResult)\n   │        └─ Runner.RunNamed(\"finalize\", taskID)\n   │           ├─ Pass CLOCHE_MAIN_RUN_ID + CLOCHE_MAIN_OUTCOME env vars\n   │           └─ Execute finalize workflow steps\n   │\n   ├─ Wait for one run to complete (completions channel)\n   └─ Backoff strategy:\n      ├─ Success: no backoff, try to fill slots immediately\n      └─ Failure or no tasks: capacityPollInterval (30 seconds) backoff\n\n4. POLLING AND STATUS TRACKING (trackRun goroutine):\n   └─ For each container run:\n      ├─ AttachOutput to container\n      ├─ Parse JSON-line protocol messages:\n      │  ├─ MsgStepStarted → RecordStepStart()\n      │  ├─ MsgStepCompleted → RecordStepComplete()\n      │  └─ MsgRunCompleted → extract results\n      └─ Wait for container exit → finalize run state\n```\n\n### 5. **Key Files and Their Roles**\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `/workspace/internal/host/loop.go` | Core orchestration loop: task polling, dedup, backoff |\n| `/workspace/internal/host/task.go` | Task types and parsing (JSONL, JSON, TaskAssigner interface) |\n| `/workspace/internal/host/runner.go` | Host workflow execution and run record creation |\n| `/workspace/internal/host/executor.go` | Host step execution, task ID env var propagation |\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` | Loop creation/enablement, container run dispatch |\n| `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` | Run record domain model and state transitions |\n| `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go` | RunStore interface: CreateRun, UpdateRun, GetRun |\n| `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go` | Daemon startup and auto-run of active projects |\n| `/workspace/cmd/cloche/poll.go` | CLI polling client (different from orchestration loop) |\n\n### 6. **Key Implementation Details**\n\n**Deduplication Strategy** (`loop.go` lines 325-346):\n- Task IDs stored in `dedup` map with assignment timestamp\n- Tasks within DedupTimeout are skipped\n- Old entries expired on each check\n- Default timeout: 5 minutes (configurable)\n\n**Backoff Strategy** (`loop.go` lines 182-270):\n- No backoff on successful runs (immediate retry)\n- 30-second backoff when no work available\n- 2-minute backoff on run failure\n\n**Run Record Persistence**:\n- Created via `store.CreateRun()` before execution starts\n- Updated on state changes: pending → running → completed\n- Step executions recorded via `RecordStepStart/Complete()`\n- Terminal state set on completion or failure\n\nThis comprehensive orchestration system enables autonomous, continuous task processing with built-in deduplication, concurrency limits, and graceful backoff."}],"totalDurationMs":41600,"totalTokens":69105,"totalToolUseCount":20,"usage":{"input_tokens":4,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4231,"cache_read_input_tokens":62174,"output_tokens":2696,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":4231},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
